 MoneyOnMobile Announces 86% Growth in Domestic Remittance and MOM ATM Revenues From April to May 
         










    











 













 











 



















MoneyOnMobile Announces 86% Growth in Domestic Remittance and MOM ATM Revenues From April to May 2017
        																																																		
              

          All product categories increase
        
















 News provided by
MoneyOnMobile, Inc.  
Jun 12, 2017, 07:20 ET









 Share this article




























































DALLAS and MUMBAI, India, June 12, 2017 /PRNewswire/ --MoneyOnMobile, Inc. (OTCQX: MOMT) today reported increases in monthly revenue across all major product categories, including an 86% increase in domestic remittance and MOM ATM revenues from April to May 2017. 








"We are excited to see continued positive growth results from our products and services. The top two lines of the chart below represent significant revenue drivers of our business. We believe our domestic remittance (money transfer) business continues to grow based on the recent line of credit increases, which allows us to increase our daily processing capacity, and strong demand for these services in our target market," said Harold Montgomery, Chairman and CEO of MoneyOnMobile, Inc.
"We are encouraged with our significant growth in the MOM ATM product. Our retailers find significant value in our MOM ATM product as a way to differentiate their business from the competition. Having a product in their store that provides cash-out services and serves as a mobile point of sale solution in a country with limited financial infrastructure cements their relationship with MoneyOnMobile," said Ranjeet Oak, Managing Director of MoneyOnMobile's India subsidiary.
Percentage Change in Revenue Categories by Transaction Type since December 2016




