MoneyOnMobile generates revenue in two ways, depending on the transaction type: either a fixed fee per transaction, or a percentage discount on the amount of the transaction. The figures above are grouped based on the commission type MoneyOnMobile receives. Domestic remittance and MOM ATM generate revenues for the retailer and MoneyOnMobile based on a fixed fee for each transaction, regardless of transaction size. Mobile and TV top-up generate revenues to retailers and MoneyOnMobile based on a percentage commission of the amount of the transaction. 
About MoneyOnMobile, Inc.
MoneyOnMobile, Inc. is a global mobile payments technology and processing company offering mobile payment services through its Indian subsidiary. MoneyOnMobile enables Indian consumers to use mobile phones to pay for goods and services or transfer funds from one cell phone to another. It can be used as simple SMS text functionality or through the MoneyOnMobile application or internet site. MoneyOnMobile has more than 330,000 retail locations throughout India. http://companiesinindia.net/top-10-ecommerce-companies-in-india.html
